notbold>33 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Dec 4th 3:52 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Sweet Tunare in the Sunshine.<br><br>OK, a reasoned and maybe reasonable reply.<br><br>&lt;Am I the only one tired of druids and rangers acting so high and mighty? Seriously folks, every other class has been taking their crap for so long and it disgusts me.&gt;<br>Uhh... OK, it is obviously the CLASS which dictates character ingame, and not the person the character is an avatar for. Right.<br><br>&lt;Does it bother anyone else that these classes are so overplayed? Not to mention the fact that these classes are also used to level up easily to make money and then twink it to another character. I don't know but I hate these weeny classes and think that they deserve something very bad. &gt;<br>CivilChief, dear, you are missing the point while you make the point. The operative verb here, phool, is PLAY.<br><br>&lt;The people who play these classes never roleplay and generally cause problems amongst lower level characters. They are easy to suck up to and con into giving you money as a lowbie. Call it being nice but I call it being stupid. &gt;<br>Hmmm... &quot;never&quot; is such a big word. My drood, Ammanita (Ammy), tries to roleplay, but I am often pounded with &quot;What class are you?&quot; &quot;What level are you?&quot; - all too often followed by &quot;Can I get a SoW?&quot; or &quot;Can you port me to...&quot;. I spend a large portion of my ingame time helping others when and where I can. Roleplaying is not respected as it should be, so saying druids don't roleplay is stupid at best. As for being &quot;easy&quot;, well I rarely if ever give out money or twink others, but if I did, and pay attention here, It Is Mine To Dispose Of As I Will. Any part of that you don't understand? As for your calling such behavior stupid, well, that you may do. Everybody has their own internal definitions for words, and if your internal lexicon equates generosity to stupidity, well, OK.<br><br>&lt;Then there is the time that we SK's get ejected out of a group so some guy's druid &quot;friend&quot; who is only his friend cause of some cash changning hands, can join. &gt;<br>Sounds like a personal problem. Let us assume it was YOU who was ejected. From what and how you write, my money would be on - you were being a @#%^ and they wanted somebody compatible with the group, and useful (see response to Eidulon below). As for the &quot;money changning [sic] hands&quot; - no comment is possible.<br><br>&lt;. And let's think about this, do either of these classes really have any true uses at higher lvls? (Yes I'm prepared to get flamed here, but I am tired of these classes and the people who play them)Come on, shaman's buff better than druids, warriors can fight better than druids, and about rangers.. what the hell can they do? Dual wield and use some of the crappier druid spells. Oh I forgot, they have track, I guess we should all just bow down to them. &gt;<br>Hmmm... lessee, any use at higher levels? Well, I doubt that a group solely consisting of SKs could take, say, Tunare - not that MY drood would ever go up against Tunare. Be interesting to see. It is the diversity of the classes that make the game fun, and it is in diverse class grouping that makes grouping interesting, and fun. Betcha forgot about that part, fun.<br>No, don't bow down to them, but utilize their strengths to augment your weaknesses as a well-played druid or ranger would utilize your strengths to augment their weaknesses.<br><br>&lt;The point I am making is that these characters survive by the easiness of their classes so they can spread their money around to make 'friends'. &gt;<br>Nope, not a valid point at all, un-substantiable and pretty stupid in content.<br><br>&lt;Nothing makes me angrier than a weeny druid (or ranger) kiting some mob across a dang zone because they take too long killing it. Not only does it end up training to someone else when the stupid druid screws it up, but the mob's other friends show up and screw everyone else over in the zone. &gt;<br>Nope, Wrong. This is a perfectly valid and appropriate technique that is NOT Unique To Druids And Rangers. Bard Fear-Kiting comes to mind. No, what all too often happens is some idiot either doesn't pay attention to what is happening just steps in and breaks the kite instead of ASKING if help is needed, or some idiot tries to KS a MoB. Are all kites well controlled? No. Do 'innocents' die in the game? Yes.&nbsp;&nbsp;BUt as a sweeping statement, very vapid, and not valid.<br><br>&lt;Well, I am finished.&gt;<br>I doubt taht very much.<br><br> &lt;I'm hoping for some allies in my argument (and war) against these two overplayed classes and I know there are many enemies out there. Sorry for the long rant&gt;<br>So, how do you _really_ feel about Druids and Rangers, huh? And, why the animosity?<br><br>Sadly, you miss the point. They are played because they are FUN. Well, my drood is, didn't like the ranger I had that much. Easy, well, yeah, sorta. But at 30 Ammy is less and less effective solo as a melee so I need to group more. And NO, this does not prove your thesis - it jsut means that the game is changing for me and I have to group more, which is one of the strengths of teh game. <br> <br><br><br><br>To quote Eidulon...<br>&lt;. <br><br>1. They can evac. Wizards can Nuke and evac. <br><br>2. They can buff. Shamans way out-buff druids, and way out-buff druids. (necros too) <br><br>3. They can heal. Clerics can way out-heal druids. &gt;<br><br>Yeah, but you get all this in ONE package. A drood makes a good backup healer, the healer to the primary healer for instance. Back up nuker too, the Planes help any summoned critter we go up against. And damage shield buffs. Melee sucks, droods get crap for weapons and armor. Yep. OK. Valid point and accepted (if not liked)limitation. But I like living by my brains rather than my brawn.<br><br>Actually, my REAL question to Civilchief ( who probably is neither), is: What the hell you doing starting this thread in a forum devoted to SKs? Talk about misplaced anger.<br><br>Hope you like walking, d00d.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
